Reasoning: The paper deals with dimensionality reduction of textual corpora, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of document-term frequency matrix and feature transformation techniques also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the exploration of different fuzzifier values for fuzzy clustering indicates a focus on optimization and algorithm design, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
